  <Docs>
    <summary>Describes the component channel bit-depths used in a Vulkan YCbCr color conversion.</summary>
    <remarks>
      <format type="text/markdown"><![CDATA[
## Remarks

`GRVkYcbcrComponents` specifies the bit-depth of each component channel used in a Vulkan YCbCr color conversion. The `R`, `G`, `B`, and `A` properties correspond to the number of valid bits in each channel as required by the `VkSamplerYcbcrConversionCreateInfo` structure.

This is a value type that does not require disposal.

## Examples

```csharp
var components = new GRVkYcbcrComponents
{
    R = 8,
    G = 8,
    B = 8,
    A = 0,
};
```
]]></format>
    </remarks>
  </Docs>
